<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Currently the docs have:</p>

<p>setGotoSimple() can be used to set a default URL to use if none is passed to gotoSimple().</p>

<p>gotoSimple() expects an action to be specified at the minimum as a first argument, so it's misleading to state that none may be passed to it.</p>

<p>It might be better to write about the setGotoXXX routines as a common set:</p>

<p>The Redirector helper can be configured with a default value for the redirection destination using the setGotoSimple, setGotoUrl, and setGotoRoute methods. Any subsequent calls to the redirectAndExit method will use the last configured destination.</p>

<p>setGotoSimple sets the destination in terms of the MVC's module, action, and controller. For example, setGotoSimple('bar', 'foo') will set up the redirection to go to /foo/bar, relative to the current host and application root.</p>

<p>setGotoUrl sets the destination in terms of the typical URL string, and setGotoRoute uses the FrontController's router to return the URL for the specified options. Assuming a route named 'profiles' had already been configured to handle requests such as <a href="http://localhost/profiles/martel">http://localhost/profiles/martel</a>, you can establish the redirect destination with a call to setGotoRoute(array('username' =&gt; 'martel'), 'profiles').</p>

